==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oleoresin
<hw>O`le*o*res"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>oleum</ets> oil + E. <ets>resin</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A natural mixture of a terebinthinate oil and a
resin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A liquid or semiliquid preparation
extracted (as from capsicum, cubebs, or ginger) by means of ether, and
consisting of fixed or volatile oil holding resin in solution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>O`le*o*res"in*ous</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oleous</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Oleose</ent>⟦br⟧
